{"id":23428,"date":"2017-05-01T15:21:12","date_gmt":"2017-05-01T19:21:12","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/blog-v2.sweeten.com\/?p=23428"},"modified":"2022-01-05T15:15:32","modified_gmt":"2022-01-05T20:15:32","slug":"putting-walls-multifunctional-spaces-privacy","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/ideas-and-inspiration\/putting-walls-multifunctional-spaces-privacy\/","title":{"rendered":"Putting up Walls for Multifunctional Spaces\u2014and Privacy"},"content":{"rendered":"<h2>How to maximize space at home: use transom windows, pocket doors, custom walls and more<\/h2>\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span class=\"s1\">Open floor plans are all the rage\u2014so much so that the first temptation of a renovating homeowner may be to tear down walls. But before you bring in the wrecking ball, consider if you&#8217;ll have enough personal space for your family (or frequent overnight guests), and how a strategically placed wall or partition can maximize your space at home while defining the private areas of your home. Take cues from these Sweeten homeowners and their clever uses of space, from carving out niches and capturing square footage in other areas to adding moveable partitions for smooth transitions.<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img decoding=\"async\" title=\"white-glass-panelled-room-divider\"  class=\"alignnone wp-image-23434 mb-24 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/Deeksha_Living_Room-05.jpg\" alt=\"white glass panelled room divider in a white living room with large windows and gray couch after renovation\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/Deeksha_Living_Room-05.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/Deeksha_Living_Room-05-723x482.jpg 723w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/Deeksha_Living_Room-05-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/Deeksha_Living_Room-05-600x400.jpg 600w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/Deeksha_Living_Room-05-585x390.jpg 585w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><img decoding=\"async\" title=\"gray-bed-storage-black-hung-window\"  class=\"alignnone wp-image-23433 mb-24 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/Deeksha_Living_Room-03.jpg\" alt=\"gray bed with storage with black double hung windows and white panelled room divider after renovation\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/Deeksha_Living_Room-03.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/Deeksha_Living_Room-03-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/Deeksha_Living_Room-03-600x400.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><br \/>\n<a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/before-after\/entire-homes\/an-interior-wall-of-windows-brings-light-to-this-guest-alcove\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Deeksha and Joe&#8217;s<\/a>\u00a0windowed wall and guest bedroom.<\/p>\n<h3>Transom windows allow for a guest bedroom to be added<\/h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With an L-shaped living room in their new apartment, Deeksha and Joe saw the opportunity to create a guest bedroom. All they needed to do was add a wall and a doorway. The only problem was that the placement of the wall would block the light and hide a gorgeous view from the corner windows. A unique solution\u2014an interior wall of windows\u2014provides the necessary privacy for the guest bedroom while still allowing the flow of light to reach the rest of the living room. The new space also serves as a light-filled workspace for the family.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" title=\"white-barn-door-white-bedroom\"  class=\"alignnone wp-image-44844 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/05\/Claire-bedroom-13-compressed-1.gif\" alt=\"white barn door to a white bedroom with large black framed windows after renovation\" width=\"1000\" height=\"674\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" \/><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/nyc\/studio-grows-into-junior-one-bedroom\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Claire and Dan&#8217;s<\/a> junior one-bedroom with sliding doors<\/p>\n<h3>Custom sliding doors to help maximize a 500 square-foot home<\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When Claire and Dan purchased their 500-square-foot studio apartment, they knew it needed a renovation. The unit hadn\u2019t been updated since the &#8217;60s, and the couple wanted to build out a junior one-bedroom by separating the living\/kitchen area from the sleeping space. With DOB regulations preventing permanent wall additions, they worked with their architect and Sweeten general contractor to install custom sliding doors. With the sliding doors, they maximize their space at home by keeping the space open during the day, and closing them for privacy or while entertaining.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-44845\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/05\/SWEETEN-LauraWalterParkinson-Apt-14_compressed.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/05\/SWEETEN-LauraWalterParkinson-Apt-14_compressed.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/05\/SWEETEN-LauraWalterParkinson-Apt-14_compressed-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/05\/SWEETEN-LauraWalterParkinson-Apt-14_compressed-600x400.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/before-after\/entire-homes\/a-brooklyn-couple-slays-the-storage-problem\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Laura and Walter&#8217;s<\/a> expanded, angular kitchen in Park Slope<\/p>\n<h3>Strategically removing a hallway adds space (and light!)<\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A long hallway was the main culprit of wasted space in Walter and Laura\u2019s Park Slope apartment. By removing their entry hallway, they imbued their apartment with more natural light<\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\u2014<\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and space. With the newly-provided footage, their kitchen swapped places with a spare bedroom and got an expanded, angular footprint in the foyer. A small dining\/entertaining area was also added to the kitchen, allowing guests to visit with the couple while they cooked. <\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/SWEETEN_Amber_Apartment-13-14.gif\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-30755 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/02\/SWEETEN_Amber_and_Chris_Transom_Window.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" \/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/SWEETEN_Amber_Apartment-22.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-23441 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/SWEETEN_Amber_Apartment-22.jpg\" alt=\"SWEETEN_Amber_Apartment-22\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/SWEETEN_Amber_Apartment-22.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/SWEETEN_Amber_Apartment-22-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/SWEETEN_Amber_Apartment-22-600x400.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/before-after\/bathrooms\/chris-ambers-bathroom-kids-room-renovation\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Chris and Amber&#8217;s<\/a>\u00a0kid&#8217;s bedroom.<\/p>\n<h3><strong>Adding a wall creates a new bedroom, while transom windows let in soft light<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The notion\u00a0of adding a dishwasher to their kitchen escalated into a full gut renovation, and then took another, unexpected turn when Chris and Amber found out their second child\u00a0was on the way. The project was now an opportunity to carve out a room for their older son. A wall was added to separate the dining nook from the rest of the kitchen, turning it into a bedroom, and a milk glass transom window was installed above the doorway to allow light to filter through. Finishing touches; a crib, picture shelves, roller blinds, and a colorful rug complete the transformation from dining nook to a growing boy&#8217;s\u00a0bedroom.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-44847 mb-24\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/05\/SWEETEN-Peter-Demoise-Kitchen_Bed-04_compressed.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/05\/SWEETEN-Peter-Demoise-Kitchen_Bed-04_compressed.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/05\/SWEETEN-Peter-Demoise-Kitchen_Bed-04_compressed-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/05\/SWEETEN-Peter-Demoise-Kitchen_Bed-04_compressed-600x400.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/> <img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-44848 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/05\/SWEETEN-Peter-Demoise-Kitchen_Bed-06_compressed.jpg\" alt=\"pocket bedroom door to maximize space at home\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/05\/SWEETEN-Peter-Demoise-Kitchen_Bed-06_compressed.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/05\/SWEETEN-Peter-Demoise-Kitchen_Bed-06_compressed-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/05\/SWEETEN-Peter-Demoise-Kitchen_Bed-06_compressed-600x400.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/before-after\/entire-homes\/a-studio-renovates-one-bedroom-hells-kitchen\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Paul&#8217;s<\/a> one-bedroom in Hells Kitchen<\/p>\n<h3><strong>A studio morphs into a one-bedroom with the help of a full dividing wall<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">New homeowner Paul landed his perfect apartment by getting creative in his search: instead of buying a \u201ctrue\u201d one-bedroom apartment in Hell\u2019s Kitchen, he purchased a studio that was listed as a junior one bedroom. Paul noticed the apartment\u2019s previous owner was already mimicking a one-bedroom layout by using a built-in bookcase to separate the bedroom and living area. He replicated this layout in his renovation by having this general contractor add a full dividing wall (with a pocket door) to separate his living area from his bedroom. <\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/SWEETEN_Frans_Apartment-08-12.gif\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-20123 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/12\/SWEETEN_Frans_Apartment-10.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/12\/SWEETEN_Frans_Apartment-10.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/12\/SWEETEN_Frans_Apartment-10-723x482.jpg 723w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/12\/SWEETEN_Frans_Apartment-10-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/12\/SWEETEN_Frans_Apartment-10-600x400.jpg 600w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/12\/SWEETEN_Frans_Apartment-10-585x390.jpg 585w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/a> <a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/SWEETEN_Frans_Apartment-27-31.gif\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-20143 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/12\/SWEETEN_Frans_Apartment-30.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/12\/SWEETEN_Frans_Apartment-30.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/12\/SWEETEN_Frans_Apartment-30-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/12\/SWEETEN_Frans_Apartment-30-600x400.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/a><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-20141 mb-24\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/12\/SWEETEN_Frans_Apartment-28.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/12\/SWEETEN_Frans_Apartment-28.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/12\/SWEETEN_Frans_Apartment-28-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/12\/SWEETEN_Frans_Apartment-28-600x400.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><br \/>\n<a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/before-after\/entire-homes\/secret-storage-and-room-for-four-in-a-contemporary-studio\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Frans and Dalal&#8217;s<\/a>\u00a0movable partitions and multipurpose spaces.<\/p>\n<h3><strong>Turning a studio into a two-bedroom (yes, really!) with movable partitions\u00a0<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Frans and Dalal planned on making their studio function as a two-bedroom; not an easy feat, considering the apartment\u2019s existing open-plan layout. They added a custom king-size platform bed in the space designated as the master bedroom. The key feature, movable partitions, allow it to work as a space for sleep or as another part of the home. For the &#8220;second bedroom,&#8221; a queen-size Murphy bed that folds up horizontally to save space and a closet were installed in the area designated as the living room, which uses the same sliding doors for privacy. As an added bonus, the wall unit that houses the pull-out bed and closet blends into the surrounding walls when the bed is tucked away.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" title=\"white-kitchen-white-peninsula\"  class=\"alignnone wp-image-44849 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/05\/DeannaDaria-kitchen-12_compressed.jpg\" alt=\"white kitchen with white peninsula and cream wall paper and brown floor after renovation\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" data-overlay-text=\"\" data-overlay-color=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/05\/DeannaDaria-kitchen-12_compressed.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/05\/DeannaDaria-kitchen-12_compressed-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/05\/DeannaDaria-kitchen-12_compressed-600x400.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/nyc\/millennial-sisters-buy-home-remodel\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Deanna and Daria&#8217;s<\/a> two-bedroom transformation<\/p>\n<h3><strong>Major wall movement reshapes an entire 700 square-foot apartment layout<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Turn one bedroom into two, create a walk-in closet, and make a dining space fit for hosting: these items topped the to-do list for sisters (and roommates) Deanna and Daria\u2019s renovation in New York\u2019s Sutton Place. To really maximize space at their home, construction moved walls from the existing dining room, living room and bedroom to reshape the new rooms: nearly the entire space of the apartment. Now, their 700 square-foot apartment maximizes every inch of space while showcasing the sisters\u2019 preference for <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">bold patterns and color. <\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/SWEETEN_Karen_Kitchen-Bathroom-11.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-23447 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/SWEETEN_Karen_Kitchen-Bathroom-11.jpg\" alt=\"SWEETEN_Karen_Kitchen-Bathroom-11\" width=\"1000\" height=\"668\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/SWEETEN_Karen_Kitchen-Bathroom-11.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/SWEETEN_Karen_Kitchen-Bathroom-11-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/SWEETEN_Karen_Kitchen-Bathroom-11-600x401.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/before-after\/entire-homes\/karen-and-kevins-apartment-renovation-sweeten-upper-west-side\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Karen and Kevin&#8217;s<\/a>\u00a0nursery.<\/p>\n<h3><strong>To maximize space at home for a new baby, walls &amp; a doorway create a nursery\u00a0<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In order to make their one-bedroom apartment family-ready, Karen and Kevin set their sights on converting a dining nook situated at the tail end of the kitchen into a nursery for their daughter. They added a new wall and doorway, which allows\u00a0 for entry from the main living area. The new nursery, now completely separate from the kitchen, receives a flood of sunlight during the day, an added benefit from the window it inherited from the former dining area.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/Sliding-Doors-No-Watermark.gif\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" title=\"living-room-with-floating-book-shelves\"  class=\"alignnone wp-image-38800 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/SWEETEN_Casey_Apartment-25.jpg\" alt=\"living room with floating book shelves and sliding doors and hardwood floors after renovation\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/SWEETEN_Casey_Apartment-25.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/SWEETEN_Casey_Apartment-25-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/SWEETEN_Casey_Apartment-25-600x400.jpg 600w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/12\/SWEETEN_Casey_Apartment-25-723x482.jpg 723w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/a><br \/>\n<a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/before-after\/entire-homes\/casey-and-kumars-clinton-hill-co-op-renovation-sweetened-part-ii-2\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Casey and Kumar&#8217;s<\/a>\u00a0retractable partition.<\/p>\n<h3><strong>A retractable partition create privacy for parents and children in a one-bedroom<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A one-bedroom in a coveted neighborhood inspired Casey and Kumar to maximize space at home for their four-person family. After examining their family\u2019s daily routines, the couple decided to give their sons the master bedroom so that they would have a space for playtime and bedtime. They added a multipurpose space in the living area with a wall of custom millwork and a pull-out bed. This became the space that Casey and Kumar could sleep and store their clothes. To preserve privacy and block light and noise, a retractable partition now divides the designated sleeping space from the rest of the home. The addition of the partition now offers flexibility for the family&#8217;s daily needs.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/SWEETEN_Linsday_Kitchen-11.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-23448 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/SWEETEN_Linsday_Kitchen-11.jpg\" alt=\"SWEETEN_Linsday_Kitchen-11\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" srcset=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/SWEETEN_Linsday_Kitchen-11.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/SWEETEN_Linsday_Kitchen-11-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/sweeten.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/SWEETEN_Linsday_Kitchen-11-600x400.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" \/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/before-after\/entire-homes\/lindsay-and-matts-sweetened-brooklyn-coop-renovation-homeowner-guest-post\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Lindsay and Matt&#8217;s<\/a>\u00a0nursery.<\/p>\n<h3><strong>Need your one-bedroom to be a two-bedroom? Demo a closet, build a partition, add a door. Voila!<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With a baby on the way, Lindsay and Matt needed to turn their one-bedroom into a two-bedroom apartment. They planned to do this by splitting the existing bedroom into a master bedroom and nursery. A few key layout changes made this all possible: demolishing closets to gain back valuable square footage, building a partition, and creating a doorway that opened into the living room. These newly constructed spaces have allowed the home to reach its full potential by making room for the whole family.<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">_<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">When planning your own private escape from the rest of the world, be sure to check out <a href=\"https:\/\/sweeten.com\/gallery\/reno-notebook\/bedroom-storage-style-renovation-ideas\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">these bedrooms<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p clas